localhost is not the same everywhere

On the host PC, localhost:1883 is the Mosquitto on that machine.
Inside a container, localhost is the container itself, not the host — so the app had to use the host’s address (e.g. Docker bridge 172.17.0.1) or the LAN IP, not localhost.
“Connection refused” to 192.168.x.x while localhost worked

Mosquitto was only listening on 127.0.0.1:1883 (loopback).
Nothing was accepting connections on the LAN IP, so remote clients got refused.
Fix: add listener 1883 0.0.0.0 (or the specific LAN IP) so the broker listens on all interfaces.


MOWBOT_MQTT_HOST=192.168.1.10 python src/main.py